{"word":"ὄξος","slug":"ὄξος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὄξος</b></el> <el>(ὄξος, εος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ὀξύς</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>poor wine, vin-de-pays</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>vinegar</i> made therefrom, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of a <i>sour fellow</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}